231
00:11:03.329 --> 00:11:07.166 
{\an8}like. making sure that it goes better
than it went last year.

232
00:11:07.834 --> 00:11:09.919  
Distraction of the show.

233
00:11:10.002 --> 00:11:11.796  
-[laughing]
-[Wagner] If you... Hey!

234
00:11:11.879 --> 00:11:14.006  
If you don't have a pencil.

235
00:11:14.090 --> 00:11:16.258  
I have 864 of them!

236
00:11:16.342 --> 00:11:18.886  
They have been mailed to me
from all over the world.

237
00:11:18.970 --> 00:11:21.347  
so I need you to come get one.
[chuckles]

238
00:11:21.430 --> 00:11:22.598  
[player] <i>Shout out to everybody on Twitter</i>

239
00:11:22.681 --> 00:11:24.308  
from all over the world.
sending us pencils.

240
00:11:24.391 --> 00:11:26.518  
Thank y'all for these pencils
that y'all sent us.

241
00:11:26.602 --> 00:11:30.022  
-'Cause we gone need 'em.
-Hey. I just need two.

242
00:11:30.106 --> 00:11:31.816  
Uh-uh. I get pencils for...

243
00:11:31.899 --> 00:11:33.735  
-He gettin' the whole thing.
-I get a pencil...

244
00:11:33.818 --> 00:11:35.611  
[Wagner] <i>I gotta figure out</i>
<i>a way to be like. "Look...</i>

245
00:11:35.694 --> 00:11:39.448  
are you gonna ruin your whole future
for two seconds of camera time?

246
00:11:39.531 --> 00:11:42.368  
Or are you gonna focus
on what you're supposed to be doing?"

247
00:11:44.829 --> 00:11:47.164  
["Annie's Song" playing on speakers]

248
00:11:48.165 --> 00:11:50.793  
<i>♪ Like a night in a forest ♪</i>

249
00:11:53.295 --> 00:11:58.426  
<i>♪ Like the mountains in springtime ♪</i>

250
00:11:58.509 --> 00:12:02.763  
<i>♪ Like a walk in the rain ♪</i>

251
00:12:04.890 --> 00:12:06.100  
[Buddy] It's a beautiful song.

252
00:12:07.059 --> 00:12:08.727  
A serenity song this morning.

253
00:12:10.729 --> 00:12:13.649  
Oh. man. it was real difficult
to watch the documentary.

254
00:12:13.733 --> 00:12:16.235  
You know. I sat back
and I watched it. and I go...

255
00:12:16.778 --> 00:12:19.488  
"I just don't like that guy.
That guy's not a good guy.

256
00:12:19.571 --> 00:12:21.698  
He's not a good coach.
[stuttering] He's a...

257
00:12:21.783 --> 00:12:25.202  
He's got...
Ooh-whee. his language is bad."

258
00:12:25.286 --> 00:12:27.288  
I met a couple in the store one day.

259
00:12:27.371 --> 00:12:29.791  
Older couple. probably in their late 70s.

260
00:12:29.874 --> 00:12:32.960  
and guy comes up to me
and introduces himself

261
00:12:33.044 --> 00:12:35.754  
and his wife is standing there
and just.

262
00:12:35.838 --> 00:12:38.340  
hey. how much they enjoyed
the documentary.

263
00:12:38.424 --> 00:12:42.845  
And I caught myself looking over at her
and saying. "I'm just... I'm so sorry.

264
00:12:42.929 --> 00:12:46.933  
[chuckles] I'm so sorry for what I said
and how I acted. and. uh...

265
00:12:47.016 --> 00:12:49.185  
just the person that I am."

266
00:12:49.268 --> 00:12:51.228  
And she said. "Coach...

267
00:12:52.479 --> 00:12:55.942  
people love sausage.
but nobody wants to see how it's made."

268
00:12:56.859 --> 00:12:59.403  
[chuckles]
And that's kind of stuck with me.

269
00:12:59.486 --> 00:13:02.865  
And she said. "You know.
people don't wanna know what reality is.

270
00:13:02.949 --> 00:13:06.785  
They don't wanna know
what it takes to keep our country safe.

271
00:13:06.869 --> 00:13:10.372  
to keep our streets safe.
to raise our children.

272
00:13:10.456 --> 00:13:13.667  
They just want 'em raised." And that's it.

273
00:13:14.418 --> 00:13:17.421  
Nobody wants to know how you do it.
They just wanna know that you do it.

274
00:13:22.134 --> 00:13:26.138  
[Tooney Hill] I really like Buddy.
I like his way of coaching.

275
00:13:26.222 --> 00:13:28.724 
{\an8}To be the best at whatever you do...

276
00:13:30.059 --> 00:13:31.560 
{\an8}you got to be different.

277
00:13:31.643 --> 00:13:34.981 
{\an8}If you're just out there.
"Come on. guys. Come on. guys."

278
00:13:35.064 --> 00:13:36.273  
That ain't gonna get it.

279
00:13:36.357 --> 00:13:39.401  
Sometimes people don't understand just...

280
00:13:41.153 --> 00:13:43.697  
um. average talk.

281
00:13:43.780 --> 00:13:47.409  
Sometimes you have to. uh.
turn it up a notch. is what I call it.

282
00:13:48.327 --> 00:13:51.163  
[Buddy Temple] <i>I said. "Wow!</i>
<i>Man. what in the world is going on</i>

283
00:13:51.247 --> 00:13:52.664  
<i>in Scooba. Mississippi?"</i>

284
00:13:52.748 --> 00:13:56.293 
{\an8}It was just such a shocking thing to me
to hear all the bad language

285
00:13:56.377 --> 00:14:00.006 
{\an8}and. I mean. I'm not blind to the fact
that kind of stuff doesn't happen.

286
00:14:00.089 --> 00:14:01.715  
but this was just overwhelming to me.

287
00:14:01.798 --> 00:14:05.928  
because this was my school
that I was listening to. my hometown.

288
00:14:06.012 --> 00:14:07.638  
<i>I didn't think it belonged there.</i>

289
00:14:07.721 --> 00:14:10.182  
<i>Buddy Stephens. he understands football.</i>

290
00:14:10.266 --> 00:14:13.102  
But I think if he went
through another season like that.

291
00:14:13.269 --> 00:14:14.311  
and did not change.

292
00:14:14.395 --> 00:14:16.480  
I think that he would be removed.
I really do.

293
00:14:17.064 --> 00:14:18.107  
[whistle blows]

294
00:14:18.190 --> 00:14:20.734  
[Buddy] Hey. let's go!
Hey. that's on me. don't worry about it.

295
00:14:20.817 --> 00:14:23.029  
That wasn't bad.
Good job. He's gotta catch the ball.

296
00:14:23.112 --> 00:14:24.780  
[Vijay Miller] I'm talking about Duck...
He ain't playing.

297
00:14:24.864 --> 00:14:26.615  
Duck's gotta catch. Hey.

298
00:14:26.698 --> 00:14:28.159  
[stuttering] Hey!

299
00:14:28.242 --> 00:14:31.162  
You understand now.
when you go into a huddle like this.

300
00:14:31.245 --> 00:14:32.621  
you just gotta pick him up.

301
00:14:32.704 --> 00:14:35.416  
He knows he missed the ball.
You just gotta pick him up now.

302
00:14:35.499 --> 00:14:39.628  
I need happy eyes. I need wide eyes.
I need having fun.

303
00:14:39.711 --> 00:14:41.172  
because that's what's gonna happen
next Thursday.

304
00:14:41.255 --> 00:14:42.298  
We're gonna have fun.

305
00:14:42.381 --> 00:14:44.758  
We're gonna move the ball
against them-- Hey!

306
00:14:44.841 --> 00:14:46.802  
You are dadgum great athletes.

307
00:14:46.886 --> 00:14:49.096  
And we're gonna move the ball
against them. okay?

308
00:14:49.180 --> 00:14:51.307  
[Crowder] <i>Buddy has an edge about him</i>

309
00:14:51.390 --> 00:14:53.350  
<i>that every winning football coach</i>
<i>has to have.</i>

310
00:14:53.434 --> 00:14:55.144 
{\an8}But I think
Buddy's also seeing some change

311
00:14:55.227 --> 00:14:57.813 
{\an8}in how maybe he deals
with people around him.

312
00:14:57.897 --> 00:14:59.773 
{\an8}deals with his players.
maybe his assistants.

313
00:14:59.856 --> 00:15:02.568  
He joked with me about the swearing.
and he said...

314
00:15:03.235 --> 00:15:06.155  
"I have to give my team five push-ups
for every swear word."

315
00:15:06.238 --> 00:15:07.781  
He said. "I've only done 15 so far."

316
00:15:08.282 --> 00:15:11.160  
Turn around.
His ass gives you... gives you...

317
00:15:11.243 --> 00:15:12.453  
"His ass."

318
00:15:13.745 --> 00:15:15.164  
[grunts]

319
00:15:15.247 --> 00:15:16.623  
[players laughing]

320
00:15:16.707 --> 00:15:18.667  
[player] Get your belly off the ground.
will you?

321
00:15:19.835 --> 00:15:22.338  
I'm gonna give ten
for what I think about you every day.

322
00:15:22.421 --> 00:15:25.591  
[Wood] <i>I think he's trying to make</i>
<i>a conscious effort to change how he talks.</i>

323
00:15:25.674 --> 00:15:27.009  
<i>and some things that he does.</i>

324
00:15:27.093 --> 00:15:29.845 
{\an8}He gets frustrated about some stuff but.
a lot of times. you know...

325
00:15:29.929 --> 00:15:32.181 
{\an8}He's... that's the way he is.
It's just his personality.

326
00:15:32.264 --> 00:15:34.141  
Everybody's got different personalities.
So...

327
00:15:34.225 --> 00:15:35.476  
[door opens]

328
00:15:36.685 --> 00:15:39.438  
-[Buddy] Hey. practice schedule!
-Yeah. I just printed it.

329
00:15:39.771 --> 00:15:40.982  
[Buddy] Did I bust you on the chops?

330
00:15:41.065 --> 00:15:42.441  
-No.
-[Buddy] I hate that.

331
00:15:42.524 --> 00:15:44.235  
-[interviewer] It's all good.
-Gotta work.

332
00:15:44.318 --> 00:15:46.570  
-Got things we gotta do.
-Printed it to the other room.

333
00:15:47.904 --> 00:15:49.198  
[Wood chuckles]

334
00:15:49.281 --> 00:15:51.575  
-But I'll re-run it.
-[Buddy sighs]

335
00:15:53.410 --> 00:15:54.745  
-Bye.
-[door closes]

336
00:15:55.704 --> 00:15:58.207  
[interviewer] But do you guys have
a good working relationship?

337
00:15:58.290 --> 00:15:59.833  
-[Wood] Yeah.
-[mouse clicking]

338
00:16:02.878 --> 00:16:03.879  
Ninth year...

339
00:16:05.005 --> 00:16:06.423  
Last man standing.

340
00:16:06.715 --> 00:16:08.550  
[laughs]

341
00:16:19.311 --> 00:16:24.150  
[Crowder] <i>EMCC looking for</i>
<i>a fourth national championship.</i>

342
00:16:24.233 --> 00:16:29.071  
<i>But that's the long-term goal.</i>
<i>because the short term is to go 1-and-0.</i>

343
00:16:29.155 --> 00:16:31.073  
<i>Jones is gonna be the first opponent.</i>

344
00:16:31.157 --> 00:16:34.576  
<i>and because of what happened last season</i>
<i>and the suspension.</i>

345
00:16:34.660 --> 00:16:37.038  
<i>there's one game where guys</i>
<i>that were on last year's team</i>

346
00:16:37.121 --> 00:16:39.623  
<i>that left the bench at the Delta game.</i>
<i>they can't play.</i>

347
00:16:49.300 --> 00:16:50.301  
[inaudible]

348
00:16:54.305 --> 00:16:56.598  
[Buddy] We'll play with half our team.

349
00:16:57.266 --> 00:17:00.811  
Uh. we'll play with
half our coaching staff.

350
00:17:01.728 --> 00:17:06.150  
We'll have to play with
half of our training staff.

351
00:17:08.235 --> 00:17:13.407  
They won't even allow the team chaplain
to come to the game.

352
00:17:13.490 --> 00:17:18.579  
We can play freshmen. we can play guys
that may have transferred. or whatever.

353
00:17:18.662 --> 00:17:23.417  
Um. but we can't play anybody that was
there at the ball game. Nobody.

354
00:17:24.085 --> 00:17:27.046  
That includes De'Andre Johnson.
who was in the press box.

355
00:17:27.129 --> 00:17:31.050  
That includes. um. managers
that were on the sideline.

356
00:17:31.133 --> 00:17:34.345  
The MACJC said that it was the whole team.

357
00:17:35.304 --> 00:17:38.014  
So it's everybody.
except for the head coach.

358
00:17:40.517 --> 00:17:42.103  
[De'Andre] I learned about two days ago.

359
00:17:42.186 --> 00:17:44.313 
{\an8}Uh. so what's that.
like a week before the game?

360
00:17:44.646 --> 00:17:48.108 
{\an8}I was kind of devastated. [chuckles]
I thought I'd be able to play. but...

361
00:17:48.275 --> 00:17:50.069  
It's all right.
Everything happens for a reason.

362
00:17:50.152 --> 00:17:51.570  
-He can't play?
-No. I can't play.

363
00:17:51.653 --> 00:17:54.740  
So I had to call my mom. my father.
everybody. Friends.

364
00:17:54.823 --> 00:17:57.576  
Canceled flights. hotels and whatnot.
so...

365
00:17:57.659 --> 00:18:01.580  
Anybody that was even in the press box.
if you just sat at that arena.

366
00:18:01.663 --> 00:18:03.540  
you can't go to the game.
you can't participate.

367
00:18:03.624 --> 00:18:05.084  
-It don't make sense.
-No sense!

368
00:18:05.167 --> 00:18:08.920  
I wish it wasn't that way.
but that's the hand that we're dealt with.

369
00:18:09.004 --> 00:18:12.007  
We're East Mississippi. we number one.
we top dog out here.

370
00:18:12.091 --> 00:18:14.510  
They could do everything they want
to hold us back.

371
00:18:19.598 --> 00:18:24.186 
{\an8}Anytime there's a bench-clearing brawl.
teams are suspended for two games.

372
00:18:24.270 --> 00:18:27.273 
{\an8}Well. we were suspended
for one game last year. the playoff game.

373
00:18:27.356 --> 00:18:30.401  
And then the first game this year.
of course. which will be the Jones game.

374
00:18:30.484 --> 00:18:33.362  
<i>Honestly. it's kind of a makeshift.</i>
<i>put-together staff.</i>

375
00:18:33.445 --> 00:18:35.989 
{\an8}<i>He'll have a new defensive coordinator</i>
<i>and a couple of defensive coaches</i>

376
00:18:36.072 --> 00:18:38.867 
{\an8}<i>but. you know. Buddy.</i>
<i>he'll be it on offense.</i>

377
00:18:38.950 --> 00:18:42.788 
{\an8}<i>because all of our coaches that were</i>
<i>on the field last year are suspended.</i>

378
00:18:42.871 --> 00:18:44.373  
<i>Now. to me. that's a bit much.</i>

379
00:18:44.456 --> 00:18:47.042  
but it is what it is. so. you know.
we'll live with it.

380
00:18:47.126 --> 00:18:49.836  
[Ed Holly] Do your job.
Hold your brother accountable.

381
00:18:49.920 --> 00:18:51.505  
Get a championship rep in.

382
00:18:51.588 --> 00:18:55.091  
Hellfire and fury is about to rain down
in Goodman now. Thursday night.

383
00:18:55.176 --> 00:18:56.885  
<i>It's a crazy situation.</i>

384
00:18:56.968 --> 00:19:00.306 
{\an8}And one. in 20-plus years of coaching.
that I've never been associated with.

385
00:19:00.389 --> 00:19:04.935 
{\an8}We're gonna be down to 28. 30 players.
compared to a 55-man roster.

386
00:19:05.018 --> 00:19:07.188  
Be accountable.
Hold your brother accountable.

387
00:19:07.271 --> 00:19:09.064  
-Understand it.
-[all] Understand it.

388
00:19:09.148 --> 00:19:10.274  
[Vijay Miller]
These bitches can't stand it.

389
00:19:10.357 --> 00:19:12.318  
Hit her on the beach. ass sandy.

390
00:19:12.401 --> 00:19:14.361  
[Ed Holly] I didn't understand
a word you said.

391
00:19:14.444 --> 00:19:16.697  
but if it dealt with
stopping the opposition. I love it.

392
00:19:16.780 --> 00:19:17.656  
Ready.

393
00:19:17.739 --> 00:19:20.451  
[Holly] <i>For me. it's exciting.</i>
<i>'cause I talk to our guys all the time.</i>

394
00:19:20.534 --> 00:19:22.869  
This is the first time
in the history of this school

395
00:19:22.953 --> 00:19:27.208  
that we're taking about a half roster
to a junior college college football game.

396
00:19:27.291 --> 00:19:29.376  
And can you imagine
when it goes successful for us?

397
00:19:29.460 --> 00:19:32.504  
These guys are gonna go down in history.
It's awesome.

398
00:19:38.552 --> 00:19:40.471  
[Wood] You need to take care
of your teammates.

399
00:19:40.554 --> 00:19:42.223  
You need to make sure
you're leading right here.

400
00:19:42.306 --> 00:19:45.058  
Don't joke around about not being
a big deal. It's a huge deal.

401
00:19:45.141 --> 00:19:46.810  
So you set the tone
with how you act today.

402
00:19:46.893 --> 00:19:48.812  
This is a bad deal
that we're at the house.

403
00:19:48.895 --> 00:19:50.397  
and you know that. and I do. too.

404
00:19:50.481 --> 00:19:53.066  
It's frustrating. Wish we were done
with it from last year's deal.

405
00:19:53.149 --> 00:19:54.235  
Unfortunately. we're not.

406
00:19:54.318 --> 00:19:55.819  
Those guys are gonna pick the torch up
and run for you.

407
00:19:55.902 --> 00:19:56.903  
ain't got to worry.

408
00:19:56.987 --> 00:19:58.239  
You need to make sure they understand it.

409
00:19:58.322 --> 00:19:59.656  
you need to make sure
you're encouragin' them.

410
00:19:59.740 --> 00:20:00.824  
the whole step of the way.

411
00:20:00.907 --> 00:20:03.994  
So make sure that you're doing
everything you're capable of doing

412
00:20:04.077 --> 00:20:06.997  
to lead this team
to a national championship.

413
00:20:07.163 --> 00:20:10.083  
Not just winning the first game.
but a national championship.

414
00:20:12.168 --> 00:20:13.295  
[Isaiah] It's dumb.

415
00:20:15.589 --> 00:20:16.965  
'Cause we only got...

416
00:20:18.425 --> 00:20:21.262  
I think. three D-linemen.
you understand.

417
00:20:23.179 --> 00:20:25.224  
And not enough offensive linemen.

418
00:20:25.307 --> 00:20:27.851 
{\an8}My very first game out of my whole life

419
00:20:27.934 --> 00:20:31.522 
{\an8}not playin' in. not startin'.
not even be able to touch the field.

420
00:20:31.605 --> 00:20:33.815 
{\an8}So it hit me. it hit me pretty deep.

421
00:20:33.899 --> 00:20:37.361  
They took it from us last year.
off some fugazi stuff.

422
00:20:37.444 --> 00:20:39.946  
<i>But. hey. it happened.</i>
<i>What happened. happened.</i>

423
00:20:40.030 --> 00:20:41.865  
We're just gonna fight
extra hard this year

424
00:20:41.949 --> 00:20:44.326  
to get what we was supposed to earn
last year.

425
00:20:52.668 --> 00:20:54.586  
[De'Andre] <i>I was like.</i>
<i>"I'm suspended too?"</i>

426
00:20:54.670 --> 00:20:57.631 
{\an8}I wasn't even on the team.
I wasn't even on the roster last year.

427
00:20:57.714 --> 00:20:59.215 
{\an8}So then why am I suspended?

428
00:20:59.300 --> 00:21:02.594  
I accepted it.
And. you know. nothin' I can do about it.

429
00:21:03.178 --> 00:21:05.555  
<i>It's been two years since I played.</i>
<i>you know.</i>

430
00:21:05.639 --> 00:21:07.391  
Adversity after adversity.

431
00:21:08.141 --> 00:21:09.685  
It's like the devil keep coming at me.

432
00:21:10.977 --> 00:21:13.564 
{\an8}<i>You know. but...</i>
[scoffs] <i>I'm cheering on Vijay.</i>

433
00:21:13.647 --> 00:21:15.899  
"Come on. Vijay. Pull this...
You know what I'm sayin'?

434
00:21:15.982 --> 00:21:18.694  
Pull this team together.
Get this win for us."

435
00:21:18.777 --> 00:21:19.986  
On the ball. the ball!

436
00:21:20.070 --> 00:21:21.530  
What's the play? Y'all know the play?

437
00:21:21.613 --> 00:21:24.533  
Go on the ball! Let's go! Get on the ball!
Get up on the ball!

438
00:21:25.116 --> 00:21:27.828  
Line up. line up!
Clock's running! Let's go. let's go!

439
00:21:27.911 --> 00:21:29.788  
Come on. man!

440
00:21:29.871 --> 00:21:32.666  
-You two were last! Danny. let's go!
-Get that thing out your ass!

441
00:21:32.749 --> 00:21:35.085  
[Trickett] <i>De'Andre knows he's the leader.</i>
<i>He's a quarterback.</i>

442
00:21:35.168 --> 00:21:36.545  
<i>They're all looking at him.</i>

443
00:21:36.628 --> 00:21:38.630  
