451
00:21:55.814 --> 00:21:58.984  
he was really focused on coming
and wanting to compete for the job.

452
00:21:59.067 --> 00:22:00.819  
And I think he's done
a marvelous job of that

453
00:22:00.902 --> 00:22:01.945  
as an incoming freshman.

454
00:22:02.028 --> 00:22:05.156  
<i>If we can keep it simple for him</i>
<i>in keepin' it where it's controlled.</i>

455
00:22:05.240 --> 00:22:07.242  
<i>where he's only got</i>
<i>one or two things to read.</i>

456
00:22:07.326 --> 00:22:08.327  
<i>then he should do well.</i>

457
00:22:08.410 --> 00:22:10.579  
[Trickett] We're better
